---
import SiteLayout from '../layouts/SiteLayout.astro';
import Icon from '../components/Icon.astro';
import Badge from '../components/ui/Badge.astro';
import Button from '../components/ui/Button.astro';
import { contractProjects } from '../data/contract-projects';
import { toolingProfiles } from '../data/profiles';
import { benchmarkSummary } from '../data/benchmarks';

const steps = [
  ['01', 'Understand', 'Capture the user, task, object, risk, state, consequence, and target.'],
  ['02', 'Resolve', 'Run design resolve so the AI receives only the relevant task packet.'],
  ['03', 'Build', 'Use DESIGN.md, mapped production components, semantic tokens, and applicable references.'],
  ['04', 'Check', 'Scan code for raw values, arbitrary styles, imports, missing semantics, and expired exceptions.'],
  ['05', 'Verify', 'Record rendered surfaces, evidence, warnings, exceptions, and visual changes in a receipt.'],
];
const publicRoutes = [
  { label: 'Home', href: '/', count: 1, description: 'Minimal discovery surface' },
  { label: 'Contracts', href: '/contracts/', count: contractProjects.length, description: 'AI-ready design packs' },
  { label: 'Docs', href: '/docs/', count: 1, description: 'Install and authoring workflow' },
];
const bundleCount = toolingProfiles.reduce((total, profile) => total + profile.bundles.length, 0);
---

<SiteLayout title="Documentation — Design Contract" description="How to install, compose, compile, verify, and share the open design contract." active="docs">
  <div class="docs-page-shell page-frame">
    <aside class="docs-sidebar" aria-label="Documentation navigation">
      <div class="docs-sidebar-section"><span>Get started</span><a class="is-active" href="#start">Introduction</a><a href="#install">Installation</a><a href="#model">Project model</a></div>
      <div class="docs-sidebar-section"><span>Authoring</span><a href="#workflow">Workflow</a><a href="#references">References</a><a href="#commands">Commands</a><a href="/contracts/">Contracts</a></div>
      <div class="docs-sidebar-section"><span>Quality</span><a href="#verify">Verification</a><a href="#benchmarks">Benchmarks</a><a href="#surface">Public surface</a><a href="#contribute">Contribute</a></div>
    </aside>
    <main class="docs-page-content">
      <header class="docs-page-header"><Badge variant="muted">Documentation</Badge><h1>Install the one-file control plane.</h1><p>Design Contract gives every AI the same authored grammar, bounded task packets, independent source checks, optional reference memory, and receipt-based verification.</p><div class="docs-header-actions"><Button href="#install" iconAfter="arrow">Get started</Button><Button href="https://github.com/byronwade/Design#quick-start" variant="outline" iconAfter="external" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">Open the README</Button></div></header>
      <div class="docs-body">
        <section id="start"><p class="eyebrow"><span class="eyebrow-rule"></span> Introduction</p><h2>One design system. Every AI. No unreviewed drift.</h2><p>This repository is both an installable package and a small reference surface. The public website is intentionally limited to home, contracts, contract details, and docs. Contract examples, Skills, references, commands, and evaluation live inside contract detail pages where the AI can use them together.</p><div class="docs-stat-grid"><div><strong>{toolingProfiles.length}</strong><span>target profiles</span></div><div><strong>{bundleCount}</strong><span>engine bundles</span></div><div><strong>{contractProjects.length}</strong><span>contract packs</span></div></div></section>
        <section id="install" class="docs-install-section"><p class="eyebrow"><span class="eyebrow-rule"></span> Setup</p><h2>Install the control plane in a project.</h2><p>Initialization creates one authored grammar, generated agent routers, hidden engine state, and an optional reference folder. It does not copy the entire engine into the product.</p><div class="command-list"><code>$ npx --yes github:byronwade/Design init --profile web-app --app-type saas-workbench</code><code>$ npx --yes github:byronwade/Design resolve --request "Add an approval workflow"</code><code>$ npx --yes github:byronwade/Design check</code><code>$ npx --yes github:byronwade/Design verify --surface approval --evidence artifacts/approval.html</code></div><div class="docs-callout"><span class="note-dot"></span><p>Start with one profile and one app type. Add another only when the product really ships across that surface.</p></div></section>
        <section id="model"><p class="eyebrow"><span class="eyebrow-rule"></span> Project model</p><h2>One authored file, generated enforcement.</h2><div class="code-line"><code>DESIGN.md</code><span>+</span><code>design/references/</code><span>+</span><code>receipts</code><span>=</span><strong>AI-ready contract</strong></div><p>The authored contract is `DESIGN.md`: product grammar, invariants, preferences, open invention space, targets, tokens, component sources, layout, states, accessibility, content, trust, mappings, references, and acceptance. Generated adapters and packets route agents through the same resolver, checker, and verifier.</p><p>Use the Mobbin-style browsing model as product inspiration: searchable surfaces, flows, patterns, screenshots, and interaction notes. Do not copy Mobbin data or ship bundled screenshot sets with the package.</p></section>
        <section id="references"><p class="eyebrow"><span class="eyebrow-rule"></span> Visual references</p><h2>Reference memory is project-owned.</h2><p><code>design/references/</code> is the local place for approved screenshots, product photos, golden states, and Mobbin-style pattern observations. Metadata and applicability belong in <code>DESIGN.md</code>. The resolver decides when those references apply.</p><div class="reference-chip-list"><span>surface</span><span>flow</span><span>pattern</span><span>interaction</span><span>source / provenance</span><span>applicability</span><span>what to preserve</span><span>what not to copy</span></div><div class="docs-inline-note"><span class="note-dot"></span><p>No default bulk download is required. Start with zero references or a small approved set, then add files when they help the AI keep a specific surface cohesive.</p></div></section>
        <section id="workflow" class="workflow-section"><p class="eyebrow"><span class="eyebrow-rule"></span> Authoring workflow</p><div class="workflow-list">{steps.map(([number, title, copy]) => <article><span>{number}</span><div><h3>{title}</h3><p>{copy}</p></div></article>)}</div></section>
        <section id="commands" class="commands-section"><p class="eyebrow"><span class="eyebrow-rule"></span> CLI</p><h2>Four public verbs, predictable output.</h2><div class="command-list"><code>$ design init --profile web-app</code><code>$ design resolve --request "Add an approval workflow"</code><code>$ design check</code><code>$ design verify --surface approval --evidence artifacts/approval.html</code></div><div class="hero-actions"><a class="text-link" href="/contracts/">Read contract packs <Icon name="arrow" size={15} /></a></div></section>
        <section id="verify" class="docs-verify-section"><p class="eyebrow"><span class="eyebrow-rule"></span> Evidence</p><h2>Proof is part of the product.</h2><div class="docs-proof-grid"><article><span>PACKAGE</span><strong>Validate the contract</strong><p>Run strict validation, tests, build, and smoke checks before sharing a change.</p><code>npm run check</code></article><article><span>BROWSER</span><strong>Inspect the rendered surface</strong><p>Keep the website small enough that the public route set can be fully inspected on every change.</p><a href="/contracts/">Open Contracts <Icon name="arrow" size={14} /></a></article><article><span>REPOSITORY</span><strong>Keep sources authoritative</strong><p>Update the owning engine file, manifest, schema, templates, skills, docs, and tests together.</p><a href="https://github.com/byronwade/Design/blob/main/.design/manifest.json" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">Read the manifest <Icon name="external" size={14} /></a></article></div></section>
        <section id="benchmarks" class="docs-benchmark-section"><p class="eyebrow"><span class="eyebrow-rule"></span> Benchmarks</p><h2>Measure component fidelity before claiming accuracy.</h2><p>The benchmark compares hidden target components to candidate outputs across anatomy, tokens, states, and content. The goal is {benchmarkSummary.targetAccuracy}% average fidelity for clean contract-plus-skills AI runs on public holdout suites.</p><div class="command-list"><code>$ {benchmarkSummary.command}</code><code>$ {benchmarkSummary.releaseCommand}</code></div><div class="docs-proof-grid">{benchmarkSummary.tracks.map((track) => <article><span>{track.label}</span><strong>{track.score}%</strong><p>{track.name}: {track.description}</p></article>)}</div><div class="docs-proof-grid">{benchmarkSummary.publicHoldoutTracks.map((track) => <article><span>{track.label}</span><strong>{track.score}%</strong><p>{track.name}: {track.description}</p></article>)}</div><div class="docs-proof-grid"><article><span>{benchmarkSummary.approvalBadgeHoldoutRun.result}</span><strong>{benchmarkSummary.approvalBadgeHoldoutRun.score}%</strong><p>{benchmarkSummary.approvalBadgeHoldoutRun.description}</p></article><article><span>{benchmarkSummary.trainedStatusBadgeRun.result}</span><strong>{benchmarkSummary.trainedStatusBadgeRun.score}%</strong><p>{benchmarkSummary.trainedStatusBadgeRun.description}</p></article><article><span>{benchmarkSummary.statusBadgeHoldoutRun.result}</span><strong>{benchmarkSummary.statusBadgeHoldoutRun.score}%</strong><p>{benchmarkSummary.statusBadgeHoldoutRun.description}</p></article></div><div class="docs-proof-grid"><article><span>{benchmarkSummary.trainedInlineAlertRun.result}</span><strong>{benchmarkSummary.trainedInlineAlertRun.score}%</strong><p>{benchmarkSummary.trainedInlineAlertRun.description}</p></article><article><span>{benchmarkSummary.trainedFilterRun.result}</span><strong>{benchmarkSummary.trainedFilterRun.score}%</strong><p>{benchmarkSummary.trainedFilterRun.description}</p></article><article><span>Public gate</span><strong>{benchmarkSummary.publicClaimEligible ? 'Open' : 'Blocked'}</strong><p><code>{benchmarkSummary.releaseCommand}</code> passes because the active approval-badge public holdout is release-eligible and above 99%.</p></article></div><div class="docs-inline-note"><span class="note-dot"></span><p>{benchmarkSummary.limitation}</p></div></section>
        <section id="surface" class="docs-surface-section"><p class="eyebrow"><span class="eyebrow-rule"></span> Explore</p><h2>Everything has a place to be read.</h2><p>The public surface keeps the Mobbin-style lesson: fast search, dense filters, browsable examples, pattern intelligence, source-linked docs, and reusable workflows without copied screenshots.</p><div class="docs-route-list">{publicRoutes.map((route) => <a href={route.href}><span><strong>{route.label}</strong><small>{route.description}</small></span><span class="docs-route-count">{route.count}<Icon name="arrow" size={14} /></span></a>)}</div></section>
        <section id="contribute" class="contribute-docs"><p class="eyebrow"><span class="eyebrow-rule"></span> Source</p><h2>Change the contract, not a duplicate page.</h2><p>New public behavior should be backed by an owning contract, schema, migration, or test. The website is only a reading surface for that source of truth.</p><a class="text-link" href="https://github.com/byronwade/Design" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">Open source <Icon name="external" size={14} /></a></section>
      </div>
    </main>
  </div>
</SiteLayout>
